item.title: IndyCar 2011 - Las Vegas Big Crash [HD] (Dan Wheldon RIP in this accident)
item.description:
IndyCar 2011 - Las Vegas Big Crash [HD] (Dan Wheldon RIP in this accident)
Colossal wreck at Las Vegas in the IndyCar finale. There are conflicting reports as to whether Dan Wheldon survived or not. No official word yet. The race was red-flagged and Dario Franchitti was declared champion for the season. Dan was going for the $5 million prize and had gained 10 spots from the back of the field in the first 12 laps. In NASCAR they always talk about "The Big One". But it was this weekend's series finale of the IndyCar Series that saw a catastrophic crash totaling 15 cars. Included in the mess was Indy 500 winner Dan Wheldon who suffered what could be serious injuries and has been airlifted to hospital. Other drivers involved in the pile-up that saw several vehicle take flight at 200-mph include James Jakes, Wade Cunningham, Paul Tracy, Vitor Meira, JR Hildebrand, Townsend Bell, Jay Howard, Tomas Scheckter, Charlie Kimball, EJ Viso, Alex Lloyd, Pippa Mann, Will Power and Buddy Rice. item.title: Dan Wheldon Tragically Killed in fiery crash at Las Vegas Motor Speedway 10/16/2011
item.description:
Dan Wheldon Tragically Killed in fiery crash at Las Vegas Motor Speedway 10/16/2011
10/16/2011 - Las Vegas Motor Speedway In a horrific 15 car crash on lap 11, Dan Wheldon was injured and later passed away at the University Medical Center in Las Vegas. Wheldon's car became airborne and then unfortunately hit the Catch Fence cockpit side first. The car then burst into flames. The remaining drivers honored him with a five car tribute lap later in the day. Dan was the winner of this year's Indianapolis 500. It was his second Indy 500 win. It was the last race of the Izod Indy Series this year and Dan was competing for the championship. Dan, born in Emberton, Olney, England, United Kingdom June 22, 1978, Passed away October 12, 2011 aged 33 years. He Leaves behind a wife Susie and 2 children, Sebastian and Oliver. Rest In Peace Dan.
